    "directionsHtml": "<h3>1. Sweeten the curd</h3><p>Whisk the thick curd with 1 tablespoon of honey until smooth and glossy. If your curd is watery, hang it in a muslin cloth for 10 minutes first — thick curd holds its layers.</p><h3>2. Build the first layer</h3><p>Take two tall glasses and spoon a layer of curd into the bottom of each. Scatter over a layer of Wefeasto Muesli, then a few banana slices.</p><h3>3. Layer again</h3><p>Repeat with more curd, more muesli and the pomegranate pearls. Aim for two or three sets of layers — the stripes are half the fun when kids peek through the glass.</p><h3>4. Top it off</h3><p>Finish with a final flourish of muesli, the chopped nuts, the remaining honey and a mint leaf. Serve straight away while the crunch is at its peak.</p>",
