    "display": "No-Bake Choco Flakes Energy Bars",
    "intro": "Tiffin-box heroes, made in one pan without switching on the oven. Wefeasto Choco's get folded into a warm peanut butter and honey binder, pressed flat, chilled and cut into bars. They are chocolatey enough that kids ask for them, and wholesome enough that you happily say yes.",
    "authorSub": "Kids recipe",
    "ingredientsHtml": "<h2>What you'll need</h2><ul role=\"list\"><li>3 cups <a href=\"/products/choco-flakes\">Wefeasto Choco's</a> (choco flakes)</li><li>1/2 cup peanut butter</li><li>1/3 cup honey (or melted jaggery for a deeper, desi sweetness)</li><li>1/4 cup roasted peanuts, roughly crushed</li><li>2 tbsp white sesame seeds (til), lightly toasted</li><li>1/2 tsp vanilla essence</li><li>A pinch of salt</li><li>1 tsp ghee, for greasing the tray</li></ul>",
    "directionsHtml": "<h3>1. Prepare the tray</h3><p>Grease a small square tray or steel dabba with ghee, or line it with butter paper leaving flaps hanging over the sides. This makes lifting the slab out later completely fuss-free.</p><h3>2. Warm the binder</h3><p>In a kadhai on low heat, stir the peanut butter and honey together for 2-3 minutes until loose and glossy. Do not let it bubble — take it off the heat and stir in the vanilla and salt.</p><h3>3. Fold in the Choco's</h3><p>Tip the Wefeasto Choco's, crushed peanuts and sesame seeds into the warm binder. Fold gently with a spatula until every flake is coated and shiny — try not to crush the flakes.</p><h3>4. Press it down</h3><p>Transfer the mixture to the tray and press down firmly with the back of a greased katori or spoon. The harder you press now, the neater your bars will cut later.</p><h3>5. Chill and cut</h3><p>Refrigerate for at least 1 hour until set firm. Lift out the slab, cut into 10 bars with a sharp knife, and store in an airtight box in the fridge for up to a week.</p>",
