    "tagText": "Kids",
    "metaLine": "Prep 10 mins · Cook 18 mins · Serves 12 cookies",
    "heroImage": "/images/wefeasto/recipe-muesli-breakfast-cookies.jpg",
    "heroAlt": "A top-down plate of golden, chewy Muesli Breakfast Cookies studded with oats, nuts and raisins, cooling on parchment.",
    "display": "Muesli Breakfast Cookies",
    "intro": "Some mornings the school bus wins the race and there's simply no time to sit and eat. These Muesli Breakfast Cookies are the happy fix — chewy, gently sweet little rounds packed with Wefeasto Muesli, ripe banana and peanut butter. Bake a batch on Sunday, tuck them into a dabba, and breakfast is sorted for the whole week.",
    "authorSub": "Kids recipe",
    "ingredientsHtml": "<h2>What you'll need</h2><ul role=\"list\"><li><a href=\"/products/muesli\">Wefeasto Muesli</a> — 2 cups (about 200 g)</li><li>Ripe bananas — 2 large, well mashed</li><li>Peanut butter — 1/3 cup (smooth, unsweetened)</li><li>Jaggery (gud) — 3 tbsp, finely grated</li><li>Whole wheat atta — 1/2 cup</li><li>Ghee or coconut oil — 2 tbsp, melted</li><li>Elaichi powder — 1/4 tsp</li><li>Raisins (kishmish) — 2 tbsp</li><li>A pinch of salt</li><li>Milk — 1 to 2 tbsp, only if the dough feels dry</li></ul>",
    "directionsHtml": "<h3>1. Warm the oven, ready the tray</h3><p>Preheat the oven to 180°C and line a baking tray with parchment or a lightly greased sheet. A warm oven means your cookies bake evenly and hold that lovely chewy centre.</p><h3>2. Mash the wet bits</h3><p>In a big bowl, mash the bananas until smooth, then stir in the peanut butter, melted ghee and grated jaggery. Mix well until it looks like a soft, glossy caramel.</p><h3>3. Fold in the good stuff</h3><p>Add the Wefeasto Muesli, atta, elaichi powder, raisins and a pinch of salt. Fold gently until everything clumps together. If it feels crumbly, add milk one tablespoon at a time until the dough just holds when pressed.</p><h3>4. Shape into little rounds</h3><p>Scoop heaped tablespoons onto the tray and flatten each slightly with the back of a wet spoon — these cookies don't spread much, so shape them the way you want them. Space them a couple of fingers apart.</p><h3>5. Bake till golden</h3><p>Bake for 16 to 18 minutes, until the edges turn golden and the tops feel set. They'll still be a touch soft in the middle — that's the chew you want.</p><h3>6. Cool, then stash</h3><p>Let them rest on the tray for 5 minutes to firm up, then move to a rack. Once fully cool, store in an airtight dabba for up to 4 days of grab-and-go mornings.</p>",
    "whyHtml": "<p>Wefeasto Muesli does the heavy lifting here — its wholegrain oats, nuts and seeds bring slow-release energy and fibre, so kids stay full through their first classes instead of crashing before lunch. The muesli also soaks up the banana and peanut butter as it bakes, giving these cookies their naturally chewy bite with barely any added sugar. Banana and jaggery keep things sweet the honest way, so it's a treat you can feel good about handing over.</p>",
    "authorBio": "The Wefeasto Kitchen team develops and triple-tests every recipe with our own cereals, so each bowl stays healthy, but tasty while being affordable. Wake up early, eat fresh & healthy.",
